Project Plan

Overview: XXXX is a web interface for sending IR signals from an LIRC server
running on a RaspberryPi.

Features:

Setup:
Parse LIRC config files to create remotes
  Get device name (option to change)
  "Buttons" (try to automate making display names out of them)
Layout a remote by dragging and dropping desired buttons
Select icon and display name for buttons
Separate view to display all buttons in the config

Admin:
Add/Edit LIRC servers
Create/Edit remotes
Users
Security

Remote features:
Custom macro buttons
Single press or long press button

Backend:
Standardize layout for common buttons
  e.g. number grids, vol+/-, chan+/-, etc.
